  <h2>You probably already know the story...</h2><br>
  <p>Forty years ago a tragedy befell the people of the village above. A kingdom in shambles, lords and ladies dead. An evil consumed the castle and it sank into the ground. The whole event was quite a bloodbath. That dark castle is still down there … Waiting.</p><p>We call it the Crimson Keep.</p><p>We all have a reason for being here in this hellish place. Prisoner. Hero. Thief. Sorcerer. I don’t know your story, and I don’t muchly care. You’ll probably die starving, wearing rags and chains, like the rest.</p><p>But, then again, maybe you’ll find treasure, or the answers you seek, or a way out? Maybe. One can hope. If I were you, I’d hope for a quick death.</p><p>*Laughter*</p><p>You’ll never escape this place, none of us will.</p><br><br>
  <p>Crimson Keep is a first person, hack n’slash, roguelike. It’s being developed by Ian Atherton (Art/Game Design) and Ben Rog-Wilhelm (Programming), with music by Matt Oglesby, and Web Design by Devon Gardner. The game began development in September 2015 using the Unity Engine.</p>
